The paper discusses the design of neural architectures and their performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of nonlinearity operations in the network, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Additionally, the paper discusses the prediction of overfitting, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
